			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Hi, </p>
<p>Great tutorial, even after finding it a couple of years after it was originally written, I found it to be quite helpful.</p>
<p>I have a question (for anybody reading this as well, not just for Rob).  Is there a relatively simple way to add a sort of &#8220;saved state&#8221; function?  To use Andrea&#8217;s mock-up as an example, if a user were to click on the &#8220;Current Exhibit&#8221; link in the navigation, is there a way to make it so that when the new page loads, the menu bar already has the &#8220;Exhibits and Events&#8221; submenu visible and the &#8220;Current Exhibit&#8221; link highlighted?</p>
