				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.puky-loopfiets.nl' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Puky loopfiets</a> </cite><a href="horizontal-dropdown-menus/comment-page-2/index.html#comment-14026"><time datetime="2012-03-16T10:44:53+00:00">Mar. 16, 2012 @ 10:44 am</time></a>				<span class="reply">
							</span><!-- .reply -->
			</header><!-- .comment-meta -->

			
			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Wow, This code is great.</p>
<p>The dropdown is good. I am trying to add some round corners to it and that worked great to. Perhaps someone else would use that to? </p>
<p>At this: </p>
<p>-webkit-border-radius: 10px;<br />
	-moz-border-radius: 10px;<br />
	border-radius: 10px;</p>
<p>to the &#8220;hover&#8221; sections. Then when you hover the menu item it will have rounded corners.<br />
good luck</p>
